          <text>
                    <body>
                              <div xml:id="d.1">
                                        <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Joannes Brecius (Bruges,
                                                  24 May 1532)</head>
                                        <floatingText type="regesta">
                                                  <body>
                                                  <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Brecius is asking what he does
                                                  here among the foreigners, in short: he would
                                                  rather live back home, among his friends, in
                                                  peace; nothing would please him more, but the
                                                  homeland has collapsed, and nothing is certain. He
                                                  would rather live here for literature than at home
                                                  in the confusion.</p>
                                                  </body>
                                        </floatingText>
                                        <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/D9537FDA-02BE-437F-ADEE-BA095961E889
                                                  "/>
                                        <p xml:id="p.1">Ad eundem.<note xml:id="note.1">According to
                                                  the previous letter, he is Joannes Brecius. We do
                                                  not know him more closely.</note></p>
                                        <p xml:id="p.2">Quaeris fortasse, quid hic agam, et cui rei
                                                  sim deditus inter nationes exteras, quarum et
                                                  mores et conditiones non noverim; brevibus rem
                                                  omnem accipe. Equidem mallem, si liceret, quietam
                                                  agere vitam in patria esse. Nihilque, mihi crede,
                                                  in hac luce contingere posset iucundius, nullam
                                                  etenim arbitror esse rem laetiorem et pleniorem
                                                  voluptatis, quam amicorum et consanguineorum uti
                                                  consuetudine, sed cum in patria omnia turbata esse
                                                  videam, et nihil usquam esse tutum, non dico ab
                                                  hostibus, sed ab internis praedonibus. Hoc
                                                  quicquid est temporis, malo hic in otio litterario
                                                  transigere, quam istic in rerum omnium
                                                  perturbatione. Vale.</p>
                                        <p xml:id="p.3"><placeName>Brugis</placeName> 24. Maii
                                                  1532.</p>
                              </div>
                    </body>
